{{Italic title|Apollo (storeship)}}
The '''''Apollo''''' is a historic [[Combat stores ship|storeship]] that is buried at a location in downtown [[San Francisco, California]].  It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1991.<ref name=nris/>  Parts of the ship have been uncovered, most recently in 1921 and 1925.  Photographs from the 1921 uncovering exist.  The 1925 [[excavation (archaeology)|excavation]] revealed coins from 1797, 1825, and 1840, a [[gold nugget]], and assorted navigational pieces.<ref name=nrhpdoc/>  One of numerous buried ships within San Francisco,<ref name=buried>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfgenealogy.com/sf/history/hgshp1.htm |title=San Francisco History: Buried Ships}}</ref> it is an [[archeological site]], listed at least partially for its potential to yield information in the future.<ref name=nrhpdoc>{{cite web|url={{NRHP url|id=91000561}} |title=National Register of Historic Places Registration: Apollo Storeship / Apollo |author=James P. Delgado |date=May 20, 1987 |publisher=National Park Service}}</ref>

[[File:NW corner Sacramento n Battery.JPG|none|thumb|Building currently at site of buried ship]]

