{{Infobox person | name = Khalifa A. AlJaziri | image = Khalifa_AlJaziri.jpg | image_size = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1979|07|23}} | nationality = [[Emiratis|Emirati]] | residence = [[Al Khawaneej]], [[Dubai]], [[United Arab Emirates]] | occupation = [[Chief executive officer|CEO]], [[E-Home Automation|e-Home AUTOMATION]]; [[Architect]], [[Entrepreneur]] | alma_mater = [[American University of Sharjah]] | spouse = Aisha AlEghfeli (2001–present) | children = 4 | signature = }}
'''Khalifa AlJaziri''' ([[Arabic]]: خليفة الجزيري; born July 23, 1979) is an [[Emiratis|Emirati]] [[entrepreneur]], co-founder of [[E-Home Automation|e-Home AUTOMATION]] and a notable<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.success.ae/?p=28|title=Khalifa Jaziri e-Home Automation}} (Arabic)</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gulfnews.com/news/gulf/uae/general/new-book-documents-emirati-success-stories-1.648046|title=Gulf News<!--INSERT TITLE--> | last = Al Lawati | first = Abbas }}</ref> [[UAE]] young business leader.
==Biography== After graduating as an Architect, and then completing his [[Masters Degree]] in [[Urban Planning]] at the [[American University of Sharjah]], AlJaziri co-founded e-Home AUTOMATION with his brother in 2003, becoming one of the first indigenous [[home automation]] and [[Computer network|networking]] companies in the [[Cooperation Council for the Arab States of the Gulf|GCC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/pushing-buttons-204720.html|title=Arabian Business Article, Pushing Buttons<!--INSERT TITLE-->
| last = Greewood | first = Aaron
}}</ref> The company has been recognized for its [[Research and development|technical innovation]] in the [[Middle East]] region by companies such as [[Intel Corporation]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ameinfo.com/150347.html |title=Intel and e-Home to build smart homes together |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121007013322/http://www.ameinfo.com/150347.html |archivedate=2012-10-07 |df= }}</ref> and [[Microsoft]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hiddenwires.co.uk/resourcesnews2009/news20090417-05.html |title=UAE-based e-Home AUTOMATION launches home automation software in the UK |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100501041655/http://hiddenwires.co.uk/resourcesnews2009/news20090417-05.html |archivedate=2010-05-01 |df= }}</ref>
AlJaziri is recognized as a leading entrepreneur in the [[United Arab Emirates|UAE]], featuring on several local [[television]] channels, including a UAE [[National Day]] special, honouring his achievements.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.homeautomationproducts.org/tag/arch-khalifa-al-jaziri |title=Sama Dubai Television interview with Khalifa AlJaziri }}{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xr4LOw3ZsYA|title=Dubai This Morning Television interview with Khalifa AlJaziri<!--INSERT TITLE-->}}</ref>
==Achievements== AlJaziri has been recognized for his achievements in the fields of entrepreneurship and [[environmentalism]], being honoured with the title [[Masdar Institute of Science and Technology]] Young Future Energy Leader.<ref>{{citation |last= |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=Episode 15: Climate Change |work=Program: Twenty Something |publisher=Dubai Media |year=2010 |url=http://www.dubaimedia.ae/Media/view/53800 |format=Television Program |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100401153605/http://www.dubaimedia.ae/Media/view/53800 |archivedate=2010-04-01 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.masdar.ac.ae/Menu/index.aspx?MenuID=16&LogDisplay=T&CatID=41&SubcatID=243&RefID=253&nextprev=4&mnu=SubCat |title=Masdar Institute Young Future Energy Leaders Gallery |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101024220544/http://www.masdar.ac.ae/Menu/index.aspx?MenuID=16&LogDisplay=T&CatID=41&SubcatID=243&RefID=253&nextprev=4&mnu=SubCat |archivedate=2010-10-24 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{citation | last = Ahmad | first = Murshed Mohammad | authorlink = | coauthors = | script-title=ar:اماراتيون .. كيف نجحوا؟ | work = | publisher = Du | year = 2010 | url = http://www.success.ae/ | format = Book | language = Arabic }}</ref>
